post_text:
Starting tomorrow, 9/11/20 ESC will be serving free breakfast and free lunch for all students. Please see below for more information.
East Sac County CSD will begin free breakfast and free lunch for all ESC students beginning Sept. 11, 2020.
The USDA provides immediate, short-term support for families by offering free meals for all children. This allows schools to serve meals to all students at no charge this fall to minimize the challenges of meal service during a pandemic. No family should have to worry about their child missing out on healthy school breakfast or lunch. This program will continue until December 31st or when USDA ends the funding.

post_text:
Information about the JV volleyball tournament at SCC this Saturday:

Calhoun County is currently classified as a COVID "hot spot". Because of this, SCC in conjunction with Calhoun County public health, have decided to implement the attached precautions for this weekend's JV volleyball tournament. Please get this information to your fans, JV volleyball players, and coaches immediately so that they can come prepared.

These precautions are only for the JV tournament in Lake City because of the smaller gym and the limited potential for social distancing. If your varsity team is playing in Rockwell City, masks are strongly encouraged but not required. The middle school has a much greater seating capacity and the opportunity to social distance is much greater.

post_text: Public health confirmed our 3rd case of a student with COVID-19 over the extended weekend. All close contacts have been notified and are to be under quarantine. Public health wants the district to stress the need to stay home with symptoms and refer to the chart- one high risk or two low risk etc (it was shared on Facebook and email from JMC). Sac County Public Health nurse, Jackie Duffy asked that parents please monitor their students closely for symptoms and reiterated the importance of the need to stay home when experiencing one high risk or two low risk symptoms. Public health also asked that we stress the importance of following quarantine and isolation. Jacque Renze, school nurse, has attached a document explaining the difference between isolation and quarantine. The district will attempt to provide a weekly update, usually on Fridays, of updated COVID cases in the district.

post_text:
East Sac County guidelines /expectations for spectators attending 2020 fall home athletic events.

1) We are doing programs for both football and volleyball

2) We are charging admission
Varsity Volleyball: $5.00 Adults $3.00 Students
JVR, JV & JH Volleyball: $3.00 Adults $2.00 Students
Varsity Football: $5.00 Adults $5.00 Students.
JVR, JV & JH Football: $3.00 Adults $2.00 Students
Requesting exact dollar amount if possible.

3) We are not limiting seating.

4) Social distancing will be highly recommended

5) Masks:
Football: Masks are not required, but highly recommended.
Volleyball: Spectators will be required to wear mask at East Sac County home volleyball matches. If a spectator does not have a mask the district will have masks for sale.
Spectators refusing to wear masks will not be admitted.

6) We are reading PA announcements and posting signage regarding social distancing and masks.
Do not attend if sick or have COVID-19 symptoms.

7) We are asking spectators have exact change at our concession stands if at all possible.

post_text: For those families choosing to have students learn from home via an online option, this information is for you. The deadline to make this decision is Wednesday, August 19th. Please contact the building principal by this time. The ESC district has decided to utilize an online curriculum hosted by EdGenuity for grades K-8 and Odysseyware for high school students. Once families choose this option, ESC will need at least a semester commitment to this learning platform because of the cost. When you contact the building principal, they will also gather information about your access to quality internet, what type of devices you have available, if you are going to continue with purchasing and picking up school breakfast and/or lunch, and contact information.

post_text:
Open House for both East Sac County Elementary and Middle Schools will be August 20 from 5:00-7:00 pm. Open House at the elementary is for any student and ONE parent whose last name starts with A-F from 5:00-5:30, G-L 5:30-6:00, M-S 6:00-6:30, T-Z 6:30-7:00. Open House at the middle school is for any student and ONE parent whose last names start from M-Z from 5:00-6:00 p.m., and those whose last names start with letters A-L from 6:00-7:00 p.m. For health and safety reasons, we ask that the following guidelines be upheld for the evening:
Only the student and ONE parent attend during the designated time (no additional family members or siblings)
Masks are recommended during this time but not required
Students are to drop off supplies and organize their lockers, meet their teachers, and exit the building—try to keep total attendance time to 15 minutes
Sanitize and wash hands as appropriate
Keep social distancing guidelines
We look forward to seeing all of our 2020-2021 students, so please attend this evening if you are able!!

East Sac County has a long history of helping the American Red Cross with blood drives. This summer there is a critical shortage of blood due to the March drive being cancelled due to COVID-19 and normal shortages of blood needed in the summer time.

The next blood drive in our ESC area will be Monday, July 6th at the Wall Lake Community Center from 11am-5pm. To make an appointment go to the website below, create or sign into your account and make an appointment or contact Lauren Litterer at llitterer21@eastsac.k12.ia.us or Lexi Boeckman at aboeckman21@eastsac.k12.ia.us.

**FOR A LIMITED TIME, THE RED CROSS WILL BE TESTING ALL BLOOD DONATIONS FOR COVID-19 ANTIBODIES AS AN ADDITIONAL SERVICE TO THEIR DONORS. THE TESTING WILL PROVIDE CRITICAL INSIGHT INTO WHETHER THE DONOR MAY HAVE HAD CORONA VIRUS.**

post_text:
East Sac County Parent/Families,

The State of Iowa would like to learn from you about technology access for you household. this information will help in planning for next school year, should learning from home need to occur because of COVID-19. East Sac County encourages you to complete this survey by JUNE 24th so your technology barriers are known to the STATE.

The survey should take less than 5 minutes, should only be taken ONCE per household, and responses only include students who will be in grades PK-12 during the 2020-21 school year.

There is a drop-down in the upper left corner of the survey to change the language from English to Spanish and make sure to select East Sac County before taking the survey.

If you have any difficulties while taking the survey, please email support_iowa@panoramaed.com.

Thank you for providing this essential information!
Please click the link below to take the survey.

post_text:
Elementary Last Day of School Drive By Wave Parade
Thursday, May 28th 6-7pm
Both East Sac Elementary buildings

Come drive by your child's elementary building and wave good-bye to the elementary teachers!

Families:
Please stay in your cars, but give all of your teachers a honk, wave, cheer, make signs, and more. Make it as fun as you’d like to celebrate your last day of school!

Please follow these routes to maintain one traffic direction:
Wall Lake: Come to the school from Stuart Street, turn east onto West 3rd Street, turn south onto Boyer Street. (clockwise around the building)
Sac City: Turn to the school from South 16th Street and follow the driveway around the school.

post_text:
Thank you East Sac County Teachers,

During this crazy time you have been asked to go above and beyond to help our students with no notice or training. You've learned how to Zoom, planned lessons to keep our student engaged at home, driven around our communities to say Hi, worried about how your students are doing and now are closing up your classrooms with no closure or good-byes to your students.

You've pushed and encouraged them to do things they didn't know they could do and supported them when things got rough. You treat your students as if they were your own and will always call them one of "my students" years down the road.

Never have we had a better opportunity to show appreciation for our teachers and what they do for our children on a daily basis. We hope all our teachers, students and families are safe and healthy at this time.

East Sac County teachers - YOU ARE APPRECIATED!

post_text:
East Sac County library book return:

During next week (April 27 -May 1), there will be a box at each of the lunch pick up locations for students and families to return their library books to the schools. You may bring your child’s (children’s) books back to any of the four lunch pick up locations, no matter what building he or she attends. Please put your book(s) in a plastic grocery sack so that it is easy for the lunch helpers to receive it from you. If there is rain, I will not have them pick up books that day.

If you can not return it during this time, there will be another opportunity during the next packet pickup for the elementary and during locker clean out for the middle school and high school students.

If you know that your child’s book is at school in their locker or the classroom, please either email me (tbettin@eastsac.k12.ia.us) or their teacher so that we can try and locate the book in the next of week. If you email me, please include your child’s grade and homeroom teacher (advisor for HS). Thank you.

Teresa Bettin
East Sac County Librarian

post_text:
IHSADA “Light Up Iowa”

The Iowa High School Athletic Directors Association (IHSADA) has invited all High Schools in Iowa to participate in a voluntary program as we seek to “Light Up Iowa” by lighting up our stadiums at 8:00 pm each Friday night. At 8:00 on Friday nights we will join together and turn on the lights of our stadiums and leave them on for one minute for each day we have been out of school.

“Light up Iowa” gives East Sac County School District an opportunity to light up the night and let our communities and students know that we miss them and look forward to having them back in our stadiums with the lights on and our communities back together.

The ESC Wall Lake and Sac City football, softball and baseball fields will be lit up starting tomorrow night.
April 10th - 15 minutes
April 17th - 20 minutes
April 24th - 25 minutes

If you would like to enjoy the stadiums "lit up" please remember to stay in your vehicles and keep social distancing.
Stay Healthy Raiders!

#Raiderstrong

Students, please check your email often as lots of important information is being sent to you and don't hesitate to reach out to a teacher or principal if you have questions or concerns.
We will get through this together. Stay home, wash your hands and keep your distance. Stay healthy Raiders!
#Raiderstrong

1. BEGINNING THURSDAY, March 19th and continuing until further notice.

Wall Lake Elementary Building: North Side (Gym Doors)

Auburn: City Hall/ library

The East Sac County Middle School is a PBIS (Positive Behavior Intervention Supports) school. One of the things we do to acknowledge positive behavior is hand out Raider Pride tickets throughout the month to students. Students can earn a ticket for having Raider Pride – being responsible, showing respect, being trustworthy and dependable, and adding a positive attitude to the school environment. Although many tickets are earned, only four tickets for each grade are drawn at the end of the month. Below are the lucky winners for the month of February.

State Farm Agent Joe McCollum in Sac City is recognizing students each month with a Student Excellence Spotlight Award. The goal of the award is to promote excellence in athletics, fine arts, and character.

Four students from the East Sac County Middle School were recognized at the end of February by their coaches and teachers.

Kinnick Fahrenkrog received the Excellence in Sports Award for Wrestling, Charlie Veit received the Excellence in Sports Award for Wrestling, Adam Frank received the Excellence in Fine Arts Award, and Carson Schmitt received the Character Award for 5th Grade. Congratulations to these students!

Last weekend East Sac County went to District speech at OA-BCIG. Here are their results!

Lyric Bussell did Public Address and earned a 1 rating, she will go to state. She performed “Kindness” by Lady Gaga.
Carley Reese did Story Telling and earned a 1 rating, she will go to state. She performed “Knifeball” by Jory John and Avery Monson
Katelyn Ryherd did Radio News Announcing and earned a 1 rating, she will go to state.
Madi Dettman did Story Telling and earned a 2 rating.

Good job Raider actors!

post_text: This week the elementary buildings are celebrating Dr. Suess' birthday with daily celebrations. Yesterday was Wacky Wednesday and the elementary students read in the hallways to encourage a love of reading.

post_text:
There is still time to sign up for the Dance Corps' Spring Show for 5-8 graders.
This is the 30th Birthday for the Dance Corps and we are hoping to include as many 5th-8th graders as possible to help celebrate this historic event. For those dancers participating, the coaches have a special opportunity beyond the dance performance!! Sign up in the office or let Connie Smith know you are interested. 515-570-4217..
conniesmith7249@gmail.com
Sign-up deadline will be extended to Thurs., March 6th or by email/phone by Friday, March 7th. Come and be part of the Dance Corps' History!!
